{
  "info": {
    "name": "Intellidine API - Production (Multi-Tenant Restaurant Management)",
    "description": "Production API collection for IntelliDine SaaS platform. Comprehensive API with 35 endpoints across 9 microservices. Includes authentication, menu management, orders, payments, inventory, analytics, notifications, and discount engine.\n\nüöÄ PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT\nüìç Base URL: https://intellidine-api.aahil-khan.tech\n‚ö†Ô∏è  Do NOT modify the base_url variable - all requests route through the API Gateway\n‚úÖ All 35 endpoints verified working\nüîê JWT Token-based authentication\nüë• Multi-tenant isolated data\n\nüìã QUICK START:\n1. Import this collection into Postman\n2. Variables are pre-configured - no changes needed to test!\n3. Start with 'Customer - Request OTP' in Authentication folder\n4. Enter any phone number (e.g., 9876543210)\n5. The system auto-creates customer on first use\n6. OTP automatically extracted and used in 'Verify OTP' request\n7. JWT token automatically saved and used in all subsequent requests\n\n‚öôÔ∏è STAFF LOGIN:\n‚Ä¢ Staff authentication requires pre-created users in the database\n‚Ä¢ To create staff users, run SQL in your database:\n  INSERT INTO users (id, tenant_id, username, email, password_hash, role, is_active)\n  VALUES (uuid_generate_v4(), '11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111', 'manager1', 'manager@spiceroute.com', '$2b$10$...', 'MANAGER', true);\n‚Ä¢ Password must be bcrypt hashed (use online bcrypt tools or your password hashing function)\n‚Ä¢ Default test credentials will be provided in your tenant setup documentation\n\nüìä TESTING FLOW:\n1. Customer OTP Flow: Request OTP ‚Üí Verify OTP ‚Üí Get JWT ‚Üí Use for API calls\n2. Staff Flow: Login ‚Üí Get JWT ‚Üí Use for API calls\n3. All endpoints automatically maintain JWT in Authorization header",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_postman_id": "intellidine-api-collection-production-v1"
  },
